m)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15082.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Paladin.....</span><hr size=1> Your starting race matters not one whit. Choose the one you like the best for any reason: stats, appearance, whatever.  <p><b>[57 Paladin] <a href="http://www.serenity-within.com/View_Member.php?Name=Aelodyn" target="_blank">Aelodyn</a> < <a href="http://www.serenity-within.com/" target="_blank">Serenity Within</a> > zone: nameless</b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 9:53:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15082.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Paladin.....</span><hr size=1> Dwarf is a good choice if I may say so myself... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>From a starting stats standpoint Dwarves get high numbers in a lot of the ones you want.  If you pick Dwarf don't make the same mistake I did and leave AGI at 70...put 5 points into it, you get a huge hit to AC if your AGI is less than 75.  <br><br>Even with that mistake it wasn't so bad, I started with STR, STA, and WIS all at or over 100.  Having STA over 100 is nice for swinging heavy weapons, which Paladins tend to do a lot.  I just kept an AGI item on me (started with a Serpentine Bracer as a lowbie and went from there).<br><br>High elf is a popular choice for clerics because of the high wisdom...with the drawback being low strength, which makes it harder (but not insurmountable) to wear heavy plate armor at the lower levels.  You also have lower stamina as well though, so you'll be taking a hit somewhere compared to Dwarf starting stats.  High INT, which high elves get, doesn't help a paladin much.<br><br>Lower strength might be particularly annoying if you ever get some of those items that have great stats except for the 10.0 or 20.0 weight on them.  At higher levels it's not so much an issue since your armor will probably have plenty of +STR on it and will most likely be a bit lighter to boot.<br><br>One positive for high elves over dwarves is that certain items aren't available to small races (Imbued Granite Spaulders, etc.) although there aren't too many examples of that.  Another is that you worship Tunare (Dwarves worship Brell) so that you can eventually quest for the Nature's Defender weapon, which some consider an easier alternative to doing the Paladin epic.  If the epic quests are extended (rumors are out there) that might not be as good of a thing, but I sure hated sitting at 52 or below to get my Vox/Naggy books.  This also might change with the release of Planes of Power--if the Plane of Underfoot is included in that there might be something nice for Brell worshippers to quest.<br><br>Half Elves also have lower STR and STA and especially low WIS for a Paladin.  They have higher CHA but CHA is overrated, I don't really even know why it's considered a &quot;primary&quot; statistic.  You also have the option of worshipping Tunare as a Half Elf so the Nature's Defender thing applies, and I believe Half Elves can wear both small and medium armor so you have more choices there.<br><br>I don't regret my decision to go Dwarf (I regret the AGI blunder but I've got enough +AGI on items to compensate for it, and if I ever wanted to shed all of the AGI items for better armor upgrades, 3 AA points could fix it).<br><br>Aalek<br>60 Crusader<br>Reign in Power<br>Torvonnilous <p></p><i>