>If you like seeing big numbers in the stat column (which you might after playing a barb warrior, if I recall correctly) dwarf is probably the way to go. Also, dwarfs are cute and do that little roll-jump thing.  Personally I've never felt being a half elf hurt me particularly (other than being encumbered if I was Master looter LOL), but I am not a stat fiend anyway.  I would go with whichever you prefer roleplaying wise or aesthetically.<br> <p>Valya Wanderfoot, 60 paladin<br><hr width="240">"I really didn'trealize the librarians were, you know, such adangerous group.... subversive. You think they're just sitting there at the desk, all quiet andeverything. They're like plotting the revolution, man. I wouldn't mess with them." --Michael Moore, 2002</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uvalyawanderfoot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valya Wanderfoot</A> at: 3/29/02 11:04:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukidkod1ak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>kidkod1ak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 204<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/29/02 11:19:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15082.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New Paladin.....</span><hr size=1> /em commando rolls into position for the pull.<br><br>Be a dwarf. Be a dwarf. Do not even consider being a gnome or halfing. Be a dwarf. <p><bold><a href = "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=101014">Varner Rapscallion</a> <br>Crusader for Brell<br> Master Brewer, Fletcher, Potter, Baker</bold></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubombuss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bombuss</A></span><br> <span class